                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the left side of the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription also in verse and in modern characters records the renovation of <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> and <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> by Śevva[ṉṉa]ṉ. The structures are stated to have been originally built by Gāṅgēyaṉ (vide No. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv17p0i0218">218</ref> above).</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
